.SH NAME
refind-btrfs-snapshots-list-snapshots - List all snapshots for detected volumes


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrefind-btrfs-snapshots list snapshots [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
List all snapshots for each detected btrfs volume.

.PP
Shows snapshot path, creation time, and parent volume for each snapshot.

.PP
Size calculation (--show-size) performance:
  • Fast: Uses btrfs quotas if already enabled
  • Slower: Falls back to native file scanning with progress indicator
  • Note: Large snapshots may take time to calculate


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for snapshots

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output in JSON format

.PP
\fB--search-dirs\fP=[]
	Override snapshot search directories

.PP
\fB--show-size\fP[=false]
	Show snapshot sizes (slower)

.PP
\fB--show-volume\fP[=false]
	Show volume column (useful for multi-filesystem setups)

.PP
\fB--volume\fP=""
	Show snapshots only for specific volume UUID or device


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is /etc/refind-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)

.PP
\fB--local-time\fP[=false]
	Display times in local time instead of UTC

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP="info"
	log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal, panic)


